[src:south-australian-national-football-league/1875-south-australian-football-season] The Club's fifth annual ball took place in the Town Hall on Friday, October 8.
[src:south-australian-national-football-league/1875-south-australian-football-season] Although the weather was rough, there were about 200 persons present.
[src:south-australian-national-football-league/1875-south-australian-football-season] The Hall was tastefully decorated with flags and evergreens, and on the platform was a small goal with a ball suspended in the centre.
[src:south-australian-national-football-league/1875-south-australian-football-season] An advertisement was placed on 19 April 1876 in the Adelaide Evening Journal titled - THE FOOTBALLER, 1875.— An Annual Record of Football.
